Note:
Rust Translator Test Suite - Comprehensive testing for Rust→HIR→Rust translation

This file provides complete test coverage for:
- Rust Lexer: Tokenization of Rust source code
- Rust Parser: AST construction from tokens
- Rust→HIR Translation: AST to HIR conversion
- HIR→Rust Generation: HIR back to Rust source
- Round-trip Testing: Verify translation fidelity

Test Coverage:
- Keywords (fn, let, mut, pub, struct, enum, impl, trait, match, etc.)
- Operators (arithmetic, logical, bitwise, range, path ::, etc.)
- Literals (integers, floats, strings, characters, byte strings)
- Lifetimes ('a, 'static)
- Type annotations (: i32, : &str, generics)
- Expressions (binary, unary, call, field access, match, closures)
- Statements (let bindings, if, while, for, loop, return)
- Items (functions, structs, enums, impls, traits, mods, use)
- Attributes (#[derive], #![feature])
- Macros (println!, vec!)
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/rust/rust_lexer.runa" as Lexer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Test Orchestration
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "run_all_rust_tests" returns Integer:
    Note: Run complete Rust translator test suite

    proc print_string with "Rust Translator Test Suite"
    proc print_newline
    proc print_newline

    Note: Lexer tests - Basic
    proc test_lexer_keywords
    proc test_lexer_operators
    proc test_lexer_literals
    proc test_lexer_lifetimes
    proc test_lexer_attributes
    proc test_lexer_numbers

    Note: Lexer tests - Advanced
    proc test_lexer_paths
    proc test_lexer_macros
    proc test_lexer_raw_strings
    proc test_lexer_byte_strings
    proc test_lexer_comments
    proc test_lexer_complex_numbers
    proc test_lexer_identifiers
    proc test_lexer_symbols

    Note: Lexer tests - Edge cases
    proc test_lexer_underscore_separators
    proc test_lexer_type_suffixes
    proc test_lexer_escape_sequences

    Note: Lexer tests - Real Rust code
    proc test_lexer_function_definition
    proc test_lexer_struct_definition
    proc test_lexer_match_expression

    Note: Integration message
    proc print_newline
    proc print_string with "All Rust lexer tests completed!"
    proc print_string with "Note: Parser, translator, and backend tests require full implementation"
    proc print_newline

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Lexer Tests
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "test_lexer_keywords" returns Integer:
    Note: Test Rust keyword tokenization

    proc print_string with "Testing Rust lexer (keywords)..."
    proc print_newline

    Let source be proc create_string_literal with "fn let mut pub struct enum impl trait match use"
    Let lexer be proc create_lexer from Lexer with source
    proc tokenize from Lexer with lexer

    Let tokens be proc get_tokens from Lexer with lexer
    Let token_count be proc size from List with tokens

    Let _kw_ok be token_count is greater than 0
    proc assert_true with _kw_ok, "Keyword tokenization produces tokens"

    Let expected_count be 11  Note: 10 keywords plus EOF
    proc assert_equals with token_count, expected_count, "Correct number of keyword tokens"

    proc destroy_lexer from Lexer with lexer
    proc print_string with "  ✓ Keyword lexer tests passed"
    proc print_newline

    Return 1
End Process

